<refnamediv><refname>imflatfield</refname><refpurpose>Correct uneven image illumination.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imflatfield(image)
out = imflatfield(image, sigma)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imflatfield</function> estimates smooth illumination, divides it out, and clips the corrected result to the normalized image range.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_left01.jpg"));
image = imresize(image, [120 160]);
out = imflatfield(image, 15);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(out);]]></programlisting></refsection>
